  "local_port": 43980,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I get bank account details from account number in SBI?",
  "response": "To get bank account details from an account number in the State Bank of India (SBI), you typically need to follow these steps:\n\n### 1. **Visit the Nearest SBI Branch**\n   - **Step 1:** Go to your nearest SBI branch.\n   - **Step 2:** Speak to a bank representative or customer service officer.\n   - **Step 3:** Provide them with the account number for which you need details.\n   - **Step 4:** You may need to provide identification and a valid reason for requesting the account details.\n\n### 2. **Use SBI Internet Banking**\n   - **Step 1:** Log in to your SBI Internet Banking account.\n   - **Step 2:** Navigate to the \u201cAccount Summary\u201d or \u201cAccount Details\u201d section.\n   - **Step 3:** Here, you can view the details of all accounts linked to your banking profile.\n\n### 3. **Use SBI Mobile App (YONO SBI)**\n   - **Step 1:** Download and log in to the YONO SBI app.\n   - **Step 2:** Go to the \u201cAccounts\u201d section.\n   - **Step 3:** Here, you can view the details of all accounts linked to your profile.\n\n### 4. **Call SBI Customer Care**\n   - **Step 1:** Dial SBI\u2019s customer care number: 1800 11 2211 (toll-free) or 1800 425 3800 (toll-free).\n   - **Step 2:** Follow the IVR instructions to connect with a customer care representative.\n   - **Step 3:** Provide the necessary details and request for the account information.\n\n### 5. **Use SBI ATM**\n   - **Step 1:** Visit an SBI ATM.\n   - **Step 2:** Insert your ATM card and enter your PIN.\n   - **Step 3:** Select the \u201cAccount Information\u201d or \u201cBalance Enquiry\u201d option.\n   - **Step 4:** The ATM will display the account details linked to the card.\n\n### 6. **Send an Email**\n   - **Step 1:** You can also send an email to SBI\u2019s customer service at contactcentre@sbi.co.in.\n   - **Step 2:** Mention your account number and request for account details.\n   - **Step 3:** Provide any additional information they might require for verification.\n\n### 7. **Check Bank Statement**\n   - **Step 1:** If you have access to the bank statement of the account, you can find the account details there.\n   - **Step 2:** Bank statements usually include the account holder\u2019s name, account number, branch details, and transaction history.\n\n### Important Notes:\n- **Privacy and Security:** SBI will not share account details with unauthorized individuals due to privacy and security concerns. You must be the account holder or have proper authorization to access the account details.\n- **Legal Requirements:** In some cases, you may need to provide a formal request or legal authorization (e.g., a court order) to obtain someone else\u2019s account details.\n\n### Final Thoughts:\nIf you are not the account holder, it is important to note that SBI will not disclose account details without proper authorization or legal documentation. Always ensure you follow the bank\u2019s protocols and respect privacy regulations.\n\nIf you are the account holder, using internet banking, the mobile app, or visiting the branch are the most straightforward methods to obtain your account details.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
